    "REASON: The proposed erection of a roof extension by reason of its poor fenestration patterns and lack of a brick built side parapets is considered to  create a harmful visual  development which would harm the existing character and appearance of the host building, the wider terrace and the surrounding Whistler Street Conservation area. The proposed development is therefore considered contrary to policy 9 of Islington’s Core Strategy 2011, D4 (Designing in context), D11 (Alterations and extensions) of Islington's Unitary Development Plan 2002, Islington’s Urban Design guidance 2006 & The Whistler Street  Conservation area guidance note."
